Hey guys I had a few questions about setting up YAGSL on MAX Swerve and was wondering if anyone could help. We have so far spent 2 weeks and whenever we run our code on advantage scope or own bot all that happens is that the rotation on each of our modules goes extremely higher (>10000) and the movement is really buggy. We’ve tried basically changing all the pids we could and changing parts of the code and nothing really works so we’re wondering if someone had a simliar issue and would be interested in reviewing or sharing code with us so we can see where we’re going wrong.

General Hard Ware Specs:
Drive Motors: Neos
Turning: Neo 550
Drive Motors are all set to medium meaning that the gear ratio is 5.08. (Some other info can be found here 3in MAXSwerve Module - REV Robotics)

Github Link:

github.com

GitHub - Coyotronics/Coyotronics2025

Contribute to Coyotronics/Coyotronics2025 development by creating an account on GitHub.

Any and all help is greatly appreciated!

YAGSL is amazing, but for rev maxswerve the template from Rev worked great for us out of the box: GitHub - REVrobotics/MAXSwerve-Java-Template. With the caveat that YAGSL implementation could yield better tuning and more of a learning experience. In terms of getting your swerve working quickly this could be a better path forward.
